# Entry Point

**Before building or modifying:**

- **Fix root cause, not workarounds:** When a bug or visual issue occurs, identify and fix the underlying cause (e.g. component logic, merge order, schema) rather than patching symptoms (e.g. inline styles, extra wrappers). Update rules to document the fix so it is not repeated.

- **When editing config/*.json:** Follow [json-syntax.mdc](./json-syntax.mdc) — no trailing commas, escape quotes in strings, run `npm run validate:json` after edits.
- **JSON config** (screens, layouts, fragments, actions): Read [docs/BUILD-GUIDE.md](../../docs/BUILD-GUIDE.md) — structure, $ref/$slot, state paths, common patterns.
- **Engine/renderer/actions** (lib/sdui/): Read [docs/CODE-ARCHITECTURE.md](../../docs/CODE-ARCHITECTURE.md) first — file map, data flow, where to add action types, **engine & performance patterns** (setNestedValue, useVariablePaths, computed memo, fetch cache LRU, searchParamSync routePrefix).

**Also:** [docs/SCHEMA.md](../../docs/SCHEMA.md) for schema (including **Section 12: Node Animation** — enter/exit/loop/hover/press, all loop types, `glowPulse`/`ripple`/`gradientDrift` rules); [sdui-layout-pitfalls.mdc](./sdui-layout-pitfalls.mdc) for layout pitfalls; [nativewind-sdui-json.mdc](./nativewind-sdui-json.mdc) for Pressable/Box text (must use Text child).

**Layout part overrides** (navbar, hero, footer override types): Read [sdui-layout-part-overrides.mdc](./sdui-layout-part-overrides.mdc) — override types, fragment ID requirements, CountdownTimer conventions.

**Visual builder** (`app/dev/builder/`, `/dev/builder`): Read [visual-builder.mdc](./visual-builder.mdc) before modifying any builder file — covers file map, design panel sections, all critical bug fixes (Button transparency, NativeWind dynamic classes, border radius per-corner tokens, flip toggle `\b` regex, exact-pixel spacing), safelist rules, and E2E test helpers.

**JSON rules:** See [json-syntax.mdc](./json-syntax.mdc). Run `npm run validate:json` after any JSON edit.
